					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Orsi wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why do we write to this address instead of $2004? </div><br />It triggers a DMA, which is the only sane way to get an entire sprite display list copied into OAM. See the bottom of <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_OAM" class="postlink">PPU OAM</a> on the wiki.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Also, I can't seem to figure out why the background colour of my rom is the 17th byte.</div>
<br />The palette entries at $3F10, $3F14, $3F18, and $3F1C don't actually exist; they're mirrors of $3F00, $3F04, $3F08, and $3F0C respectively. (During normal rendering, $3F04, $3F08, and $3F0C are ignored.) So when you write $3F10, you overwrite the background color in $3F00.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

